    "notes": "G8 IV subgiant Sun-analog (1.06 Msun, 1.12 Rsun) — exceptionally inactive (log R'HK = -5.13, well below solar minimum -4.96; Gomes da Silva 2021 weighted mean of 6002 HARPS spectra). No direct interferometric diameter (declination -66) so radius from PARSEC isochrone (1.115 +/- 0.025 Rsun, Gomes 2021). Bruntt 2010 quoted R = 1.22 +/- 0.02 from L+Teff Stefan-Boltzmann with older Hipparcos parallax + Teff = 5604 K — Phase 3 markdown cites this as 'asteroseismic + interferometric' but no asteroseismology paper for delta Pav has been published and there is no interferometric measurement; that Phase 3 basis attribution is incorrect and the divergence with current Phase 2 (1.115 vs 1.22, ~9%) traces to (a) updated parallax and (b) PARSEC vs Stefan-Boltzmann method choice. Rotation P_rot = 175 +/- 30 d is an upper limit derived from Ramirez 2013 v sin i = 0.32 km/s + R = 1.115 Rsun assuming i = 90 deg (the HARPS vsini detection floor); true P_rot may be longer. Age 5.04 +/- 1.23 Gyr (Gomes 2021 PARSEC isochrone) is the young end of the literature spread — Bensby 2014 also gives ~5 Gyr, but Tsantaki 2013 and Eiroa 2013 Ca II age both give 8-9 Gyr. Adopt 5 Gyr per tier hierarchy (newest paper, smallest uncertainty) but flag this is contentious. X-ray non-detection (ROSAT, Hunsch 1998) gives log L_X < 26.6 cgs (i.e. log(L_X/L_bol) < -7.08), consistent with the very low log R'HK; not added as a separate activity_measurements entry since log_rhk is higher tier and a single recommended is set."
  }
